SUMMARY: Winnie-the-Pooh
DESCRIPTION:\nAbout Theatre in the Grove’s production of Winnie-the-Pooh\
 n\n\nThis production of Winnie-the-Pooh is an amazing\, heart-felt adapta
 tion\, by Sean Patrick Nill\, of the original stories by A.A. Milne.\n\nN
 ew to the neighborhood and feeling out of place\, Christopher Robin would
  rather retreat into his room than face the unfamiliar world outside. Whi
 le a friendly neighbor tries to draw him into play\, he finds comfort ins
 tead in his cherished stuffed animals. Sensing his son’s unease\, A.A. Mi
 lne begins sharing imaginative stories inspired by those beloved toys—sto
 ries filled with adventure\, warmth\, and gentle humor. As the tales unfo
 ld\, Christopher Robin discovers the confidence to step beyond his fears 
 and connect with others. Drawn from A.A. Milne’s original work\, Winnie-t
 he-Pooh brings timeless characters to life onstage and reminds audiences 
 of all ages that friendship often begins with a little courage.\n\nDirect
 ed by Donald Cleland with assistant director/stage manager Kathleen Lacoc
 k\, the cast of this production is mostly youth\, ages 8 to 20.\n\nThere 
 are 6 performances open to the public: Feb 6 & 13 @ 7:30PM\, Feb 7\, 8\, 
 14\, 15 @ 2:30PM.\n\n
CATEGORIES:live-theatre,all-ages,children,community-theatre
