SUMMARY: Eugenie Jones at Jack London Revue
DESCRIPTION:Seattle-based jazz vocalist\, songwriter\, and captivating li
 ve performer Eugenie Jones will take the Jack London Revue stage in Portl
 and on Friday\, February 20\, 2026.\n\nRenowned for her distinctive “smok
 e & satin” vocals\, electric stage presence\, and emotionally resonant so
 ngwriting\, Jones has earned international acclaim for live performances 
 that seamlessly blend inventive takes on vintage jazz\, soulful original 
 compositions\, and classic R&B.\n\nJones is a two-time Earshot Jazz Vocal
 ist of the Year\, the first vocalist to win the Earshot Jazz Album of the
  Year award. Her sixth and current album\, **EUGENIE **\, charted on the 
 Jazz Week Top 50 for 25 weeks\, peaking worldwide at #4.\n\nEugenie has g
 raced the stages of Denver’s Dazzle Jazz Club\, the Atlanta Jazz Festival
 \, Minton's Playhouse in New York\, the San Jose Jazz Festival\, Ann Arbo
 r’s Blue Llama Jazz Club\, Earshot Jazz Festival\, Seattle Arts Musuem\, 
 the Royal Room\, the National Jazz Museum in Harlem\, the San Jose Jazz F
 estival and numerous others\n\nShe will be joined by an exceptional trio 
 featuring Nick Allison (piano)\, Jonathan Green (bass)\, and Greg Campbel
 l (drums).\n\nStream her Jazz Week #4 ranked release - "EUGENIE" - at eug
 eniejones.bandcamp.com/album/eugenie-2 https://eugeniejones.bandcamp.com/
 album/eugenie-2
