SUMMARY: PSU Choirs: A South African Celebration with Michael Barrett
DESCRIPTION:Featuring world-renowned guest composer and conductor Michael
  Barrett from South Africa in an extraordinary citywide choir collaborati
 on\, this concert is a powerful celebration of community\, growth and mus
 ical storytelling. As Portland State University’s choral program has expa
 nded\, this performance reflects the deep roots and far-reaching branches
  of our shared choral ecosystem. Highlights will include many of Michael 
 Barrett's best-known arrangements of South African music\, like "Indodana
  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Eb7Ooxl9srQ&list=RDEb7Ooxl9srQ&start_rad
 io=1 " and "Inkosi Namandla https://youtu.be/oIOvvAayFXY?si=KyNNdWUHEDneh
 79n \," plus Ethan Sperry's new arrangement of the Oscar-winning Bollywoo
 d song "Naatu Naatu" from RRR and Coty Raven Morris's new composition "Ta
 pestry of Stars."\n\nPSU’s Chamber Choir\, Rose Choir and Thorn Choir are
  joined by a massed choir of 200 of the finest high school singers from a
 cross the Portland area\, including students from these high schools: Gra
 nt\, Lincoln\, Sam Barlow\, Camas\, Rex Putnam\, Gresham and Cleveland. T
 his concert will be a once-in-a-generation gathering of voices across age
 s and experiences. Expect music that challenges and uplifts—music that re
 minds us how\, when voices come together\, our shared soil becomes someth
 ing profoundly alive.
CATEGORIES:live-music,choir,south-african-music,choral-music
