SUMMARY: PSU Theater Arts presents: Spring Awakening
DESCRIPTION:Spring Awakening is a riveting rock musical that captures the
  desires\, pain\, excitement\, and confusion of adolescence. Set in a rig
 id and repressive society\, it follows a group of teenagers as they navig
 ate the treacherous terrain of growing up—confronting sex\, pregnancy\, l
 ove\, loss\, and the suffocating pressures of school and family.\n\nAs th
 ey struggle to make sense of their inner lives and relationships\, these 
 young characters reach for connection\, discover the power of their voice
 s\, and push back against the conservative forces that seek to silence th
 em.\n\nDriven by Tony Award-winning alternative rock score by Duncan Shei
 k\, the music of Spring Awakening pulses with the urgency\, defiance\, an
 d yearning of adolescence. Spring Awakening offers a powerful and poignan
 t theatrical experience that resonates deeply with audiences of every gen
 eration.\n\nThursday\, February 26\, 7:30 PM (Preview performance\, $15 t
 icket discounts available\nFriday\, February 27\, 7:30 PM (Opening night!
  Join us for a post-show reception with the company.)\nSaturday\, Februar
 y 28\, 7:30 PM\nSunday\, March 1\, 2:00 PM\n\nWednesday\, March 4\, 7:30 
 PM (Community night: Arts workers\, PSU community and alumni receive $10 
 tickets)\nThursday\, March 5\, 7:30 PM\nFriday\, March 6\, 7:30 PM\nSatur
 day\, March 7\, 2:00 PM\n\n\nSpring Awakening is presented through specia
 l arrangement with Music Theatre International (MTI). All authorized perf
 ormance materials are also supplied by MTI. http://www.mtishows.com
CATEGORIES:theater,performing-arts,musical,live-performance
