SUMMARY: The Little Mermaid: The 80s Pop Ballet
DESCRIPTION:WORLD PREMIERE Dive into a neon-drenched\, upbeat reimagining
  of a classic story—and a Broadway-meets-ballet experience like you’ve ne
 ver seen before. Ballet Fantastique’s long-awaited Little Mermaid: An 80s
  Pop Ballet is the latest project from award-winning BFan Choreographer-P
 roducers Donna Marisa and Hannah Bontrager—set to a live\, electrifying s
 oundtrack of iconic ’80s hits performed by hip new LA band Neon Revival.\
 n\nMeet Eileen\, a brave young mermaid with defiant dreams and a voice th
 at stops time. When she makes a daring pact with the cunning sea sorceres
 s Roxanne (“Come On\, Eileen”!)\, Eileen joins a human world bursting wit
 h high-stakes romance\, synth beats\, and unexpected transformation. This
  is your happily ever after…with a twist! Featuring all-new choreography\
 , era-inspired 80s couture by some of the PNW’s most visionary designers\
 , and a vibrant fusion of pop nostalgia with BFan’s signature theatrical 
 storytelling\, Little Mermaid: The ’80s Pop Ballet is a bold addition to 
 the company’s genre-defying new dance theater canon.\n\nPerformances: Sat
 . Feb. 28 - 7:30 pm / Sun Mar. 1 - 2:30pm\n\nLive music: original arrange
 ments & LIVE MUSIC:Neon Revival (LA)
CATEGORIES:dance,ballet,kids,family
