SUMMARY: CSA Share Fair
DESCRIPTION:Want to Eat More Veggies? Love Local? Try Community Supported
  Agriculture (CSA)!\n\nIn a time when food insecurity is on the rise and 
 industrial food systems continue to dominate\, families can join a CSA to
  make a renewed commitment to eating more veggies\, while strengthening t
 heir community\, supporting small farms with sustainable agricultural pra
 ctices and building local food resilience.\n\nNot sure where to start? Ev
 ery CSA program is different\, and with nearly 100 CSA farms in the regio
 n\, PNWCSA can help you find a farm (or farms!) that best fits your eatin
 g habits. Bring the kids and enjoy a family-friendly event filled with fu
 n activities. From farmer matchmaking to a cookbook swap and silent aucti
 on\, this event is all about discovering the benefits of CSA and meeting 
 the people behind the food. Attendees that purchase a CSA share using SNA
 P get 50% off fruits and vegetables.\n\nReal food\, real connections—that
 ’s what CSA is all about. This is a free event.\n\n
CATEGORIES:local-farms,eat-local,csa,community-supported-agriculture
