SUMMARY: Forest Grove High School Student Directed One Act “Lockdown”
DESCRIPTION:Good evening!!!\nmy name is Carl McMahon\, I am 17 years old 
 and I am extremely passionate about theater and the impact it makes on pe
 ople’s lives. I am messaging you on behalf of Thespian Troupe #5712.\nFor
 est Grove high school is putting on a one act production called “Lockdown
 ”. Lockdown is fully student directed and focuses on events within Americ
 a right now.\nSummary: “In a dark classroom\, eight students sit in an “o
 fficial lockdown\,” not knowing if it’s just a drill or an actual emergen
 cy. When a hysterical younger girl bolts from the room and the teacher fo
 llows\, the remaining students are left alone to decide if it’s safer to 
 stay or run.”\nAll proceedings from Lockdown will go to Troop #5712 and w
 ill help get our competitors to Oregon Thespians State Competition in Apr
 il\nThespians State Competition is a 3-day event featuring over 1\,000 st
 udents\, hundreds of educational workshops\, one-act plays\, and competit
 ions. This gives our troupe members college opportunities and scholarship
 s\, as well as direct training from real world professionals in preformin
 g and tech. We have the privilege to go this year and would love your sup
 port on our funding.\nOur request is a post or something like that on you
 r page or somewhere where it would be viewed a lot because we know it wou
 ld gain a ton of traction and hopefully bring in a huge audience.\nThis i
 s a one night only event on March 17th at 6pm at Forest Grove High School
 .\nRecommended for ages 13+ due to sensitive topics and language\n\n\nPle
 ase see our thespians instagram https://www.instagram.com/fgvikingtheatre
