SUMMARY: Matthias Kemeny Lecture Series Presents April Greiman
DESCRIPTION:The Kemeny Lecture Series\, launched in 2019 with an endowmen
 t from the Matthias Kemeny Estate\, is a monthly talk series hosted by PS
 U’s Graphic Design Program. Each discussion features a renowned designer 
 who is invited to talk about their practice and share their insights on t
 he world of design. April Greiman–a pioneering designer and transmedia ar
 tist who helped shape a new visual language for design–will speak on Apri
 l 9\, 2026. Having worked across publications\, environments\, and digita
 l media\, Greiman transformed the computer from a production tool into a 
 creative instrument.\n\n
