SUMMARY: The Oregon Garden "EARTH DAY" Celebration
DESCRIPTION:The Oregon Garden is honored to welcome the community to its 
 2026 Earth Day Celebration on Saturday\, April 18\, from 10:00 am to 4:00
  pm. In celebration of the Garden’s 25th anniversary\, admission is FREE 
 for all guests\, inviting families\, friends\, and neighbors to enjoy a f
 ull day of nature\, learning\, and hands-on discovery across 80 acres of 
 botanical beauty.\n\nThis milestone year offers a meaningful moment to re
 flect on a quarter‑century of stewardship\, community partnership\, and e
 nvironmental education. The Earth Day celebration brings together exhibit
 ors\, workshops\, and family‑friendly activities designed to spark curios
 ity and inspire sustainable living.\n\n\nEvent Highlights\n\n  * Educatio
 n Exhibitors: Connect with 20+ local nonprofits and eco‑conscious busines
 ses offering conservation tools\, resources\, and practical guidance.\n  
 * Workshops & Education: Take part in hands‑on demonstrations that introd
 uce simple\, approachable ways to live more sustainably.\n  * Explore the
  Garden: Wander through specialty gardens and managed wetlands on a self‑
 guided walk\, or enjoy a narrated tram tour.\n  * Family Activities: Chil
 dren can explore nature‑themed crafts\, meet friendly animals\, and engag
 e with interactive learning stations that nurture environmental stewardsh
 ip.\n  * Music & Food: Enjoy offerings from local food vendors and a vibr
 ant cultural performance by the Monmouth Taiko Drummers.\n\n“Earth Day is
  one of our favorite traditions\, and this year feels especially meaningf
 ul as we celebrate 25 years of caring for the Oregon landscape\,” said De
 len Kitchen\, Executive Director at The Oregon Garden. “We’re thrilled to
  welcome the community for free and offer a place where families can lear
 n\, explore\, and grow their love for the environment together.”\n\n\nEve
 nt Details\n\nDate/Time: April 18\, 2026 | 10:00 am – 4:00 pm\n\nAdmissio
 n: Free\n\nOn‑Site Parking: $10 (free for Garden members)\n\nPark & Walk:
  Complimentary lots available at the Silverton Senior Center and Robert F
 rost Elementary\n\nThis FREE event\, open to the community\, is made poss
 ible thanks to the support of our valued community partners\, including L
 eafGuard\, Earthlight Technologies\, and Highway Fuel Company.\n\nFor mor
 e information\, please visit www.oregongarden.org http://www.oregongarden
 .org\n\n
CATEGORIES:Community,Family-Friendly,Entertainment,Hands-on-activities
