SUMMARY: Gladstone Arbor Day & Plant Sale
DESCRIPTION:Join the Friends of Gladstone Nature Park on April 25\, 2026 
 for our 10th Annual Arbor Day & Plant Sale in the Gladstone Nature Park\,
  18111 Webster Road in Gladstone.\n\nThe sale runs from 9am to 3pm and in
 cludes: Oregon native plants\, vegetable starts\, hanging baskets\, peren
 nials\, kitchen herbs\, mushroom grow-kits\, free seeds for sharing\, fru
 it and berry plants\, local honey\, tool sharpening\, soil testing\, free
  kids books\, electronics recycling and concessions.\n\nMany special plan
 ts from Willamette Valley nurseries will be featured. The Clackamas Count
 y Library will offer their free seed collection. Kraxberger Robotics team
  will recycle your electronics. Gladstone High School students will offer
  herbs from their greenhouse program. Gladstone Baseball Association will
  have refreshments to purchase to support their teams. We will have our b
 eautiful hanging baskets for Mother’s Day again.\n\nAre you doing a nativ
 e garden or Backyard Habitat? We will have abundant varieties of native p
 lants to get you started and experts on hand to advise you.\n\nThe event 
 is free and parking is available at the LDS church at 8331 Cason Road\, i
 n Gladstone. Please use the crosswalk. The park is served by TriMet bus l
 ines 31 & 32. Proceeds support restoration projects in the Gladstone Natu
 re Park. A can or 2 of food for our local food bank is much appreciated!\
 n\nFor more information\, contact: FriendsOfGladstoneNature@gmailcom mail
 to:FriendsOfGladstoneNature@gmailcom?subject=Plant%20sale .
CATEGORIES:
