SUMMARY: As You Like It: A Wild West Ballet
DESCRIPTION:MOTHER’S DAY WEEKEND: Saddle up to experience an unforgettabl
 e adventure. Ballet Fantastique’s As You Like It: A Wild West Ballet is a
  bold\, high-spirited twist on one of the most classic love stories of al
 l time—with cowboy boots\, barroom brawls\, and a hoedown finale.\n\nChor
 eographed by dynamic mother-daughter duo Donna and Hannah Bontrager\, thi
 s unique dance theater original features a cinematic\, genre-fusing custo
 m Wild West score for BFan by Grammy®-nominated international composer Ju
 an Luqui (Netflix\, Hulu\, Nat Geo\, Playstation). And in a one-of-a-kind
  twist\, the whole story is hilariously narrated in Shakespearean verse—d
 elivered with a Western drawl by the sharp-tongued Touchstone (with UO Sh
 akespeare professors Lynn Freitas and Rachel Hanan). No advance reading r
 equired.\n\nPerformances: THU\, MAY 7\, 2026 – 7:00 pm / FRI\, MAY 8\, 20
 26 – 7:30 pm / SAT\, MAY 9\, 2026 – 7:30 pm/ SUN\, MAY 10\, 2026 – 2:30 p
 m
CATEGORIES:dance,ballet,music,live
