SUMMARY: Gathering in the Garden--Celebrating Gardening and the Appreciat
 ion of Community Green Spaces
DESCRIPTION:Gathering in the Garden:\n\nCelebrating Gardening and the App
 reciation of Community Green Spaces\n\nSaturday\, May 16\, 2026 Eastmorel
 and Garden Park\n\n10 AM - 2 PM Corner of SE Bybee Blvd & 27th Ave.\n\nPo
 rtland\, OR 97202\n\nEnjoy live music and a Silent Auction while shopping
  for organic tomato starts\, indoor/outdoor shrubs and plants\, garden ar
 t\, ceramics\, handcrafted leather and canvas bike bags and shopping tote
 s\, new and used garden accessories. The Eastmoreland Neighborhood Associ
 ation will offer engraved memorial bricks to be installed at the Garden. 
 Children can learn how to pot their own plants at the supervised Children
 ’s Corner. The Portland Rose Society will sharpen hand pruners\, one per 
 customer\, free of charge.\n\nVENDORS: Kelly Posch Pottered and Pieced Po
 ttery\, Out in the Garden Nursery\, Lords Luggage\, Wake Robin Native Pla
 nt Gardening\, Cobb Hoelzer Pottery Studio\, Cascadia Plant Company\, and
  Pamela Winklesky of Winkworx Art.\n\nNON-PROFITS: Portland Rose Society\
 , Multnomah County Master Gardeners\, Eastmoreland Neighborhood Associati
 on 100 Trees for 100 Years Committee\,\n\nFriends of Portland Community G
 ardens\, Sellwood Community House\, Sellwood Middle School PTA\, Duniway 
 Elementary School PTA.\n\nMUSIC: The OC Ukers\, Pacific Rose Ensemble\, S
 ellwood Middle School Jazz Band\, 13th Moon Irish Session\, and Sellwood 
 Moreland Ukulele Revival Club (SMURK).\n\nALL ARE WELCOME!\n\nPresented b
 y Eastmoreland Garden Club and co-sponsor\, Eastmoreland Neighborhood Ass
 ociation\, with support from District Four Coalition (D4C):\n\nNeighbors 
 West Northwest (NWBNW).
